context: The party was a member of the <b0_0>Labour and Socialist International<b0_0/> between 1923 and 1940. However, in <b2_0>February 2013<b2_0/>, the Labour Party NEC decided to downgrade participation to observer membership status, "in view of ethical concerns, and to develop international co-operation through new networks".
